      • setupCaptures

        protected CaptureSearchResults setupCaptures(int closestIndex,
                                 Resource... resources)
                                      throws Exception
        given a sequence of WarcResources,
        • build CaptureSearchResults, filled with CaptureSearchResult instances, which have auto-generated unique filename and offset of 0. this is necessary for equality (see AccessPointTest.CaptureSearchResultMatcher).
        • setup ResourceStore mock to return Resource for each CaptureSearchResult.
        • setup ResourceIndex mock to return CaptureSearchResults.
        • if closestIndex >= 0, set corresponding CaptureSearchResult's closest flag, and also set up ReplsyDispatcher.getClosest() mock to return it.
        Parameters:
        closestIndex - 0-based index of resource to be marked as closest
        resources - sequence of WarcResources
        Returns:
        CaptureSearchResults built
        Throws:
        Exception

      • testHandleRequest_Replay_1

        public void testHandleRequest_Replay_1()
                                throws Exception
        test basic behavior 1.
        • no authorization
        • no exclusion factory
        and,
        • there's no capture on date matching the request.
        • closest capture is not a revisit
          • this shall result in redirect (302) response to the URL with closest capture date in date component. alternative path: testBounceToReplayPrefix()
        Throws:
        Exception
